description: From mag +‎ -s- +‎ man, of unclear origin. It has been suggested that mag was dialect for halfpenny or for prattle.

entries.meaning: (archaic) A con man who tries to deceive members of the public.
examples: […]  M was a Magsman, frequenting Pall-Mall; / N was a Nose that turned chirp on his pal;  […]
